the use of fortran in subroutines with cobol main programs.wby using the proper cobol coding techniques andaccounting for differences in storage allocation and library routines between the two languages, it ispossible to write fortran iv subroutines that may be called from cobol main programs.  such a techniqueenables the programmer to take advantage of the most useful properties of each language whileminimizing their respective disadvantages.cacm april, shavell, z. a.ca jb march ,   : pm